'''121局'''（{{lang|en|Bureau 121}}）<ref name=arc/>成立於1998年<ref name=nyt1/>，是北韓軍事力量[[網絡戰|網絡戰]]的一部分，與其同儕[[朝鮮第91所|91所]]<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.businessweek.com/news/2014-12-07/sony-s-darkseoul-breach-stretched-from-thai-hotel-to-hollywood | title = Sony's Breach Stretched From Thai Hotel to Hollywood | first1 = Jordan | last1 = Robertson | first2 = Dune | last2 = Lawrence | first3 = Chris | last3 = Strohm | date = 7 December 2014 | work = Bloomberg News | publisher = Bloomberg Businessweek | accessdate = 2015-12-14 | archive-date = 2014-12-07 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20141207215632/http://www.businessweek.com/news/2014-12-07/sony-s-darkseoul-breach-stretched-from-thai-hotel-to-hollywood | dead-url = no }}</ref>
共隸屬於[[朝鲜人民军|北韓軍方]]所轄的[[朝鲜人民军总参谋部侦察总局|朝鲜人民军总参谋部侦察总局]]並廣為人知
<ref name = reuters>{{cite web | url= http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/12/05/us-sony-cybersecurity-northkorea-idUSKCN0JJ08B20141205 | first1= Ju-Min | last1= Park | first2= James | last2= Pearson | title= In North Korea, hackers are a handpicked, pampered elite | publisher= [[Reuters|Reuters]] | date= December 5, 2014 | accessdate= December 18, 2014 | archive-date= 2015-10-11 | archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20151011082231/http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/12/05/us-sony-cybersecurity-northkorea-idUSKCN0JJ08B20141205 | dead-url= yes }}</ref><ref name=guardian>{{cite web|last1=Gibbs|first1=Samuel|title=Did North Korea's notorious Unit 121 cyber army hack Sony Pictures?|url=http://www.theguardian.com/technology/2014/dec/02/north-korea-hack-sony-pictures-brad-pitt-fury|work=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]|date=December 2, 2014|accessdate=January 20, 2015|archive-date=2019-12-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191203143201/https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2014/dec/02/north-korea-hack-sony-pictures-brad-pitt-fury|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

據美國當局消息，朝鮮偵查總局下有六個分支部門，負責主導朝鮮的秘密作戰（{{lang|en|clandestine operation}}）及情報蒐集任務。<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.fas.org/irp/world/dprk/ | author=John Pike | title=North Korean Intelligence Agencies | publisher=Federation of American Scientists, Intelligence Resource Program | date= | accessdate=January 20, 2015 | archive-date=2021-01-26 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210126152529/https://fas.org/irp/world/dprk/ | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=arc>{{cite web|url=http://www.fas.org/irp/world/dprk/dod-2013.pdf|author=[[United_States_Department_of_Defense|United States Department of Defense]]|title=Military and Security Developments Involving the Democratic People's Republic of Korea 2013|publisher=Federation of American Scientists|date=|accessdate=January 20, 2015|archive-date=2021-03-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210309023225/https://fas.org/irp/world/dprk/dod-2013.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>
網絡戰爭被視為朝鮮恃以維持其非對稱({{lang|en|asymmetric}}）軍事力量且經濟有效的途徑之一，其首要目標涵括[[南韓|南韓]]、[[日本|日本]]及[[美國|美國]]等。

121局全體成員均享有朝鮮國內最高層次的待遇。朝鲜政府自本國数学、計算機等領域甄选了大量尖端人才，加以嚴苛培訓後選取其中最優者作為網絡部隊新血，據悉選拔淘汰率逾98%。

==編制==
援引[[路透社|路透社]]報導，由朝鮮軍方主持的121局全員均為國內極出色的計算機專家<ref name=reuters/>。一名曾與121局學員共事的[[脫北者|脫北者]]稱該機構僱員總數超過1800人，分佈於全球各個角落，其中大多數人於位居平壤的[[自動化大學|自動化大學]]畢業後被分配到此機構<ref name =reuters/>。作為享有的優渥待遇之一，他們的家人被當局特許遷至首都[[平壤|平壤]]定居——據[[CNN|CNN]]報導，只有值得信賴的、健康的和忠誠的“精英”才能生活在平壤。<ref name=wh>{{cite news | url = http://wwlp.com/2014/12/19/white-house-viewing-sony-hack-as-national-security-threat/ | title = White House viewing Sony hack as national security threat | first = Jim | last = Sciutto | work = CNN | publisher = WWLP 22 News | date = 19 December 2014 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141219121315/http://wwlp.com/2014/12/19/white-house-viewing-sony-hack-as-national-security-threat/ | archivedate = 2014年12月19日 | df =  }}</ref>

==任務與手段==
2014年12月，[[索尼音樂娛樂|索尼音樂娛樂]]因其計算機受到黑客組織“和平守衛者”（Guardians of Peace）的[[索尼影業遭黑客攻擊事件|非法入侵]]而取消了其所攝製的電影“[[採訪_(電影)|採訪]]”的首映式。<ref name= variety-interviewdropped>{{cite web |title= Major U.S. Theaters Drop 'The Interview' After Sony Hacker Threats |url= http://variety.com/2014/film/news/major-u-s-theaters-drop-the-interview-after-sony-hacker-threats-1201381861/ |website= Variety |accessdate= December 17, 2014 |last1= Lang |first1= Brett |archive-date= 2020-11-12 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20201112034736/https://variety.com/2014/film/news/major-u-s-theaters-drop-the-interview-after-sony-hacker-threats-1201381861/ |dead-url= no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.cnn.com/2014/12/18/politics/u-s-will-respond-to-north-korea-hack/ | first1 = Pamela | last1 = Brown | first2 = Jim | last2 = Sciutto | first3 = Evan | last3 = Perez | first4 = Jim | last4 = Acosta | first5 = Eric | last5 = Bradner | title = U.S. will respond to North Korea hack, official says | publisher = [[CNN|CNN]] | date = December 18, 2014 | accessdate = December 18, 2014 | archive-date = 2020-12-07 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201207224126/https://www.cnn.com/2014/12/18/politics/u-s-will-respond-to-north-korea-hack/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>121局被認為是此次攻擊的實施者，朝鮮當局則矢口否認該部隊對攻擊負有責任。<ref name = abc />

“和平守衛者”多次攻擊的目標均指向[[南韓|南韓]]<ref name = reuters /><ref name=arc/>。在發起針對索尼的攻擊前，朝鮮被認為攻擊了南韓境內至少三萬台計算機，禍及銀行機構、廣播公司和大韓民國總統[[朴槿惠|朴槿惠]]的宣傳站點<ref name = reuters /><ref name=arc/><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-25/s-korea-president-s-websites-closed-for-review.html | author=Sangwon Yoon, Shinyye Kang | title=S. Korea Government, Media Sites Hacked Closed for Review | publisher=[[Bloomberg_News|Bloomberg]] | date=June 25, 2013 | accessdate=December 20, 2014 | archive-date=2014-12-26 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141226075136/http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-25/s-korea-president-s-websites-closed-for-review.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>，並應當為其在2013年利用賭博程式夾帶惡意代碼、感染南韓境內成千上萬部智能手機的行徑負責<ref name=abc>{{cite news | url = http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/sony-hack-believed-routed-infected-computers-overseas/story?id=27667840 | title = Sony Hack Believed to Be Routed Through Infected Computers Overseas | first = Jack | last = Cloherty | work = ABC News | place = US | date = 17 December 2014 | publisher = Go | accessdate = 2015-12-14 | archive-date = 2020-11-11 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201111200650/https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/sony-hack-believed-routed-infected-computers-overseas/story?id=27667840 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。[[賽門鐵克|賽門鐵克]]（{{lang|en|Symantec}}）認為，由10至50名於網站滲透方面各具“專長”的成員構成的黑客組織'''{{lang|en|DarkSeoul}}'''是[[2013年南韓網路攻擊|2013年南韓網路攻擊]]的幕後實施者<ref name=reuters/>。

美國方面認為北韓擁有發起國家級網絡攻擊的能力，其在網路的惡意活動自2009年後即持續進行至今<ref name=arc/>。作為秘密體系的一部分，121局的分支被確信分佈並活躍於全世界範圍內。<ref name=wh/><ref>{{cite episode | series = [[The_Lead_with_Jake_Tapper|The Lead with Jake Tapper]] | first = Jake | last = Tapper | network = CNN | airdate = 18 December 2014 | url = http://thelead.blogs.cnn.com/2014/12/18/panel-is-north-korea-waging-a-cyberwar | title = Panel: Were North Korean "cyber soldiers" behind Sony hack? | access-date = 2015-12-14 | archive-date = 2021-03-26 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210326012906/https://thelead.blogs.cnn.com/2014/12/18/panel-is-north-korea-waging-a-cyberwar/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>相當多的證據顯示，位於中國瀋陽的[[七寶山饭店|七寶山饭店]]（已关闭）很可能曾经是121局的前哨據點之一<ref>{{cite web |url=http://origin.www.uscc.gov/sites/default/files/Research/China's%20Position%20on%20the%20Sony%20Attack_0.pdf |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2015年12月14日 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151020060623/http://origin.www.uscc.gov/sites/default/files/Research/China%27s%20Position%20on%20the%20Sony%20Attack_0.pdf |archivedate=2015年10月20日 |df= }}</ref><ref name=nyt1>{{Cite web |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2015/01/19/world/asia/nsa-tapped-into-north-korean-networks-before-sony-attack-officials-say.html?_r=1 |author=David E. Sanger, Martin Fackler |title=N.S.A. Breached North Korean Networks Before Sony Attack, Officials Say |publisher=[[nytimes.com|nytimes.com]] |date=January 18, 2015 |accessdate=January 20, 2015 |archive-date=2020-11-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108163702/http://www.nytimes.com/2015/01/19/world/asia/nsa-tapped-into-north-korean-networks-before-sony-attack-officials-say.html?_r=1 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=Chilbosan>{{cite news|last1=Daly|first1=Michael|title=Inside the 'Surprisingly Great' North Korean Hacker Hotel|url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2014/12/20/inside-the-surprisingly-great-north-korean-hacker-hotel.html|accessdate=25 December 2014|agency=The Daily Beast|date=December 20, 2014|archive-date